Title: Joseph Woodward | Software Engineer & Go lover based in Somerset, England
Description: For a while now I’ve been keeping a close eye on the structure logging proposal making its way through Go’s language proposal process. Last month an experimental version of the proposal was released under the golang.org/x/exp package (see documentation here) and I decided to experiment with it and decided to summarise my learnings in a blog for others to learn more about this proposed addition to the Go standard library.

Title: Drones to protect civilians and Communication equipment
Description:
These funds will purchase thermal vision drones for the Ukrainian 92nd brigade.
- 5 Thermal vision DJI Mavic 2 Enterprise Advanced drones
- 5 DJI Mavic 3 FMC drones
- Motorola SLR5500 VHF repeater

The brigade protects the civilian population and liberates villages around Svatove.

We will also purchase a radio repeater for better coordination between the Ukrainian Liberators

Title: Pie-Stop for Pi-Hole | planetkris
Description: Just setup a pi-hole for DNS filtering. I subscribed to a bunch of block lists and then subsequently prevented Christine from loading a site on her work laptop. Seeing as how the network admin is not always home to take care of issues like this, I wanted a way for anyone in the house to disable filtering for ~5 min. There are many, many, many IoT button tutorials out there, with lots of different hardware, so this post will cover light details, please use it for inspiration.
